## Documentation Guidelines

### Code Documentation
- Add doc comments to public APIs
- Explain complex logic with inline comments
- Document function parameters and return values
- Include usage examples where helpful

### README and Guides
- Start with a clear overview
- Include installation/setup instructions
- Provide usage examples
- Document configuration options
- Add troubleshooting section if relevant

### API Documentation
- Document all endpoints/functions
- Include request/response examples
- Explain error codes and handling
- Provide authentication details if applicable

## Writing Style

- **Be concise**: Get to the point quickly
- **Be accurate**: Verify all technical details
- **Be helpful**: Think about what users need to know
- **Be consistent**: Follow existing documentation patterns

## Completion Criteria

Mark your subtask complete when:
- [ ] All specified documentation is written
- [ ] Examples are tested and working
- [ ] Documentation follows project conventions
- [ ] No broken links or references

## Output

When complete, provide:
1. Documentation files created/modified
2. Key sections documented
3. Examples added
4. Any areas needing follow-up
